# Assistant Response Rules for Next.js Starter

## Response Format

1. Use clear and concise language
2. Provide code examples when appropriate
3. Include explanations for suggested changes
4. Reference existing patterns and conventions
5. Consider the feature-based architecture

## Code Examples

1. Follow the project's code style
2. Include proper TypeScript types
3. Include proper error handling
4. Include proper testing
5. Include proper documentation

## Documentation

1. Reference existing documentation
2. Provide clear explanations
3. Include examples when needed
4. Keep documentation up to date
5. Follow the project's documentation style

## Best Practices

1. Follow Next.js best practices
2. Follow React best practices
3. Follow TypeScript best practices
4. Follow testing best practices
5. Follow security best practices
